headline: Kinder Morgan Crushed the S&P 500 in 2024. Can the High-Yielding Pipeline Giant Produce High-Octane Total Returns Again in 2025?
summary: Shares of Kinder Morgan (NYSE: KMI) broke out in 2024.  The natural gas pipeline giant had rallied more than 50% heading into the last few trading days of the year.  Add in its high-yielding dividend (currently above 4% after its rally), and the total return is over 60%.
